* Choose the Right\nSharing Protocol
** Databricks-to-Databricks
***_ Recipient has UC-enabled workspace
***_ Platform-managed authentication
***_ Share via sharing identifier
***_ Tables, views, volumes, notebooks, models
** Open sharing
***_ Any platform (non-Databricks)
***_ Bearer tokens or OIDC
***_ Manual token lifecycle management
***_ Tables only
** Decision factors
***_ Recipient platform type
***_ Token management capability
***_ Asset types to share
***_ Performance requirements
** Mixed recipients
***_ Create multiple recipient objects
***_ One per access pattern
@endmindmap
